Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The increase in numbers of cases to 191, with 8 new cases in 24 hours, and more yellow fever (YF) fatalities is serious. Collection of garbage may be helpful in eliminating the breeding sites for the vector mosquitoes, but initiation of a comprehensive vaccination campaign is urgent. YF has been spreading around the country in recent days. Although 70 percent of the population reportedly has been vaccinated previously, obviously there are enough unvaccinated susceptible individuals to sustain ongoing transmission and spread.

Maps of Angola can be accessed at http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4012749,165; of Viana in relation to Luanda at http://becoangola.com/imagens/viana.gif. - Mod.TY]
